<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[835,1443,1141,1814]" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">
has been reported from 
<collectingRegion box="[1014,1073,1178,1202]" country="United States of America" name="Ohio" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">Ohio</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="DeWalt" box="[1090,1317,1178,1202]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="DeWalt" pageId="9" pageNumber="39" pagination="1" refId="ref9082" refString="DeWalt, R. E., Y. Cao, T. Tweddale, S. Grubbs, L. Hinz, M. Pessino &amp; J. Robinson. 2012. Ohio USA stoneflies (Insecta, Plecoptera): species richness estimation, distribution of functional niche traits, drainage affiliations, and relationships to other states. ZooKeys, 178, p. 1. https: // www. ncbi. nlm. nih. gov / pmc / articles / PM C 3317619 / pdf / ZooKeys- 178 - 001. pdf" type="journal article" year="2012">DeWalt et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
), southern 
<collectingRegion box="[835,925,1214,1238]" country="United States of America" name="Indiana" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">Indiana</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="DeWalt &amp; Grubbs" box="[956,1282,1214,1238]" firstAuthor="DeWalt" pageId="9" pageNumber="39" pagination="31 - 50" refId="ref8927" refString="DeWalt, R. E. &amp; S. A. Grubbs. 2011. Updates to the stonefly fauna of Illinois and Indiana. Illiesia, 7 (3): 31 - 50. http: // illiesia. speciesfile. org / papers / Illiesia 07 - 03. pdf" type="journal article" year="2011">DeWalt &amp; Grubbs 2011</bibRefCitation>
), and from 
<collectingRegion box="[835,993,1250,1274]" country="United States of America" name="Pennsylvania" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">Pennsylvania</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion box="[1042,1127,1250,1274]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">Florida</collectingRegion>
west to 
<collectingRegion box="[1244,1360,1250,1274]" country="United States of America" name="Louisiana" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">Louisiana</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P." pageId="9" pageNumber="39" pagination="437 - 445" refId="ref11172" refString="Stark, B. P. 1986. The Nearctic species of Agnetina (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 59: 437 - 445. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / pdf / 25084804. pdf" type="journal article" year="1986">Stark 1986</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P." box="[911,1051,1286,1310]" pageId="9" pageNumber="39" pagination="437 - 445" refId="ref11172" refString="Stark, B. P. 1986. The Nearctic species of Agnetina (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 59: 437 - 445. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / pdf / 25084804. pdf" type="journal article" year="1986">Stark (1986)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the distribution of this species was similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pictet, 1841)" baseAuthorityName="Pictet" baseAuthorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Acroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arenosa">
<emphasis box="[1146,1355,1322,1346]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">Acroneuria arenosa</emphasis>
(Pictet, 1841)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Banks, 1902)" baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[960,1345,1358,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Paragnetina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumosa">
<emphasis box="[960,1177,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">Paragnetina fumosa</emphasis>
(Banks, 1902)
</taxonomicName>
, both of which have been reported from 
<collectingRegion box="[1250,1344,1394,1418]" country="United States of America" name="Georgia" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">Georgia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ricker" firstAuthor="Ricker" pageId="9" pageNumber="39" pagination="279 - 288" refId="ref10969" refString="Ricker, W. E. 1949. The North American species of Paragnetina (Plecoptera, Perlidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 42 (3): 279 - 288. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 42.3.279" type="journal article" year="1949">Ricker 1949</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stark &amp; Gaufin" box="[907,1165,1430,1454]" firstAuthor="Stark" pageId="9" pageNumber="39" pagination="221 - 253" refId="ref11509" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; A. R. Gaufin. 1976. The Nearctic species of Acroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 49 (2): 221 - 253. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / pdf / 25082817. pdf" type="journal article" year="1976">Stark &amp; Gaufin 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Specimens presented here were collected nearly 80 years ago by the late Dr. P.W. Fattig. Described as a “tireless collector” (
<bibRefCitation author="Lund" box="[844,993,1538,1562]" firstAuthor="Lund" pageId="9" pageNumber="39" pagination="352" refId="ref10521" refString="Lund, H. O. 1954. Perry Wilbur Fattig 1881 - 1953. Journal of Economic Entomology, 47 (2): 352. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jee / 47.2.352" type="journal article" year="1954">Lund 1954</bibRefCitation>
) the former Emory University entomologist made many contributions to the documentation of various insect groups from 
<collectingRegion box="[835,932,1646,1670]" country="United States of America" name="Georgia" pageId="9" pageNumber="39">Georgia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
